Romania, Hungary and Slovakia have been ordered to play their next home matches in Euro 2020 qualifying behind closed doors due to racist behaviour from their supporters, UEFA announced on Monday. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1259829" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/UEFA.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" />European football’s governing body announced Romania’s next two fixtures on their own turf will have to take place in a near-empty stadium, the second of which is suspended subject to a one-year probationary period. They were also handed an 83,000 euro ($91,000) penalty for incidents which included racist chanting as well as field invasions during games against Spain and Malta earlier in the month. Cosmin Contra’s side play Norway in Bucharest on October 15 and welcome Sweden a month later in the Romanian capital in their two next homes games. UEFA decided the one-match ban for the other two countries following incidents in the Slovaks’ 2-1 Group E victory in Budapest on September 9. Hungary, who were given a penalty of 67,125 euros, welcome Azerbaijan on October 13, the Slovakians, who were fined 20,000 euros, host Wales in Trnava three days earlier. VANGUARD Didier Drogba will be allowed to play in Galatasaray's Champions League clash against Schalke after the German club had their objections over his eligibility thrown out by UEFA on Wednesday. February 28, 2013 In "Sports" The Danish Football Association (DBU) is looking for replacements for regular national team players for this month’s matches against Slovakia and Wales after contract negotiations broke down. September 3, 2018 In "Sports" Belgium on Wednesday moved a friendly international against Portugal away from Brussels after the militant attacks on the city while UEFA said it has "contingency plans" for the European Championships in France. March 24, 2016 In "Sports"